        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <p>
            Michael Jackson, also known as the "King of Pop," was a legendary American singer, songwriter, and dancer. He was born on August 29, 1958, in Gary, Indiana, and became one of the most influential and iconic figures in the history of music.
        </p>
        <h2>Legacy</h2>
        <p>
            Michael Jackson's impact on the music industry and pop culture is unparalleled. He released numerous chart-topping albums, including "Thriller," which remains the best-selling album of all time. His innovative music videos, including "Billie Jean" and "Thriller," set new standards for the industry.
        </p>
